    "description": {
      "value": "<p>When you cast <em>hobble mount</em> as a successful melee spell attack against a horse, wolf, or other four-legged or two-legged beast being ridden as a mount, that beast is disabled so that it can't move at its normal speed without incurring injury. An affected creature that moves more than half its base speed in a turn takes 2d6 bludgeoning damage.<br>This spell has no effect on a creature that your GM deems to not be a mount.<br><em><strong>At Higher Levels.</strong></em> When you cast this spell using a spell slot of 2nd level or higher, the damage increases by 2d6 for each slot level above 1st.",
